; =============================================================================
; ARCHITECTURE: Monroe 2890 / Compucorp 32x (4-bit BCD Processor)
; FILE: monroe_2890_cartridge_chopped.txt.a.bin
; =============================================================================
; INSTRUCTION KEY:
; lbl   - External Entry Point or Label
; tml   - Subroutine Call (Transfer and Mark)
; tm/tl - Jump (Transfer)
; lbua  - Load B Register Upper Address (Pointer Setup)
; lb    - Load B Register (Memory Address Pointer)
; ld    - Load Register into Accumulator
; ldi   - Load Immediate value to Accumulator
; t     - Transfer Accumulator to Register
; exd   - Exchange Digit (Swaps accumulator with a specific memory digit)
; ex    - Exchange Register (Swaps accumulator with entire register)
; adc   - Add with Carry (Essential for BCD math)
; rtnsk - Return and Skip (Conditional return logic)
; sf1   - Set Flag 1 (Usually indicates error or specialized state)
; =============================================================================

; --- SECTION 1: SYSTEM ENTRY TABLE ---
; The calculator OS jumps to these addresses when cartridge keys are pressed.
0000: 00 8E            lbl 8e        ; Function Entry 1
0002: 00 98            lbl 98        ; Function Entry 2
0004: 00 E5            lbl e5        ; Function Entry 3
0006: 00 E9            lbl e9        ; Function Entry 4
0008: 00 F9            lbl f9        ; Function Entry 5
000A: 00 FC            lbl fc        ; Function Entry 6
000C: 00 FC            lbl fc        ; Function Entry 6 (Alternate)

; --- SECTION 2: INITIALIZATION & CONDITIONAL LOGIC ---
000E: 01 07            tml 07        ; Call setup routine at 07
0010: 04               lbua          ; Setup B-Register pointer
0011: 32               ld 2          ; Load Register 2
